title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
OB: When calling getcolumnlabel from meta data object before data extraction, it does not return user recognizable strings.
EB: The getcolumnlabel function from meta data object should return the same user recognizable labels both before and after data extraction. This is crucial for displaying consistent labels to end users.
SR:
1. Initialize meta data object with column labels.
2. Call getcolumnlabel before data extraction.
3. Verify that the returned labels are user recognizable and match the labels after data extraction.
